line_1: There is a prurience in the speech of some,
line_2: Wrath stays him, or else God would strike them dumb;

line_1: On others eagles spread their wings; on some
Some Swearing Loud, and Others Laughing; Some
line_2: Were always Talking, Others always Dumb.

line_1: I, here wha sit, hae met wi' some,
Some griev'd for past, for future Mischiefs some:
line_2: Mean while our melancholy Fleet steers Home,

line_1: Yet so unskilful or so fearful some,
line_2: For nine that speak there's nine-and-forty dumb.

line_1: Wit pardons Faults, since every one has some;
line_2: If ye are Envious, vent it all at home,
